# TcIO Interface File Format

Interfaces are stored in `.TcIO` files using the `<Itf>` element. They define method and property contracts without implementation.

## XML Structure

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1" ProductVersion="3.1.4024.16">
  <Itf Name="I_Example" Id="{GUID}">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[INTERFACE I_Example
]]></Declaration>
  </Itf>
</TcPlcObject>
```

## Methods (inside Itf)

Interface methods have Declaration only — no Implementation section:

```xml
    <Method Name="Start" Id="{GUID}">
      <Declaration><![CDATA[METHOD Start : BOOL
VAR_INPUT
    nMode : INT;
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
    </Method>
```

## Properties (inside Itf)

### Read-write property (Get + Set) — 3 GUIDs

```xml
    <Property Name="DisplayName" Id="{GUID}">
      <Declaration><![CDATA[PROPERTY DisplayName : STRING
]]></Declaration>
      <Get Name="Get" Id="{GUID}">
        <Declaration><![CDATA[]]></Declaration>
      </Get>
      <Set Name="Set" Id="{GUID}">
        <Declaration><![CDATA[]]></Declaration>
      </Set>
    </Property>
```

### Read-only property (Get only) — 2 GUIDs

```xml
    <Property Name="IsEnabled" Id="{GUID}">
      <Declaration><![CDATA[PROPERTY IsEnabled : BOOL
]]></Declaration>
      <Get Name="Get" Id="{GUID}">
        <Declaration><![CDATA[]]></Declaration>
      </Get>
    </Property>
```

## Key Differences from POU

| Aspect | POU (`<POU>`) | Interface (`<Itf>`) |
|--------|---------------|---------------------|
| Root element | `<POU Name="..." Id="..." SpecialFunc="None">` | `<Itf Name="..." Id="...">` |
| ST declaration | `FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_Name` | `INTERFACE I_Name` |
| Implementation | Has `<Implementation><ST>` | No implementation section |
| Methods | Have Declaration + Implementation | Declaration only (no Implementation) |
| Properties | Get/Set have Declaration + Implementation | Get/Set have Declaration only (empty CDATA) |
| Actions | Supported | Not supported |
| SpecialFunc | Required (`"None"` default) | Not present |

## GUID Count

| Element | GUIDs needed |
|---------|:------------:|
| Interface itself | 1 |
| Method | 1 |
| Property (read-write) | 3 (Property + Get + Set) |
| Property (read-only) | 2 (Property + Get) |

See `twincat3-xml-tcpou.mdc` GUID Rules for format, generation, and uniqueness requirements.

## Rules

- Interface names use `I_` prefix: `I_Controller`, `I_EB_BA_Widget`
- `Name` attribute must match the INTERFACE name inside CDATA
- Methods in interfaces have **no** `<Implementation>` section — only `<Declaration>`
- Property Get/Set in interfaces have empty `<Declaration><![CDATA[]]></Declaration>` — no Implementation
- Exception: A Set accessor may have a VAR block in its Declaration if local variables are needed for validation in the implementing FB
- Never add `SpecialFunc` to `<Itf>` — that attribute only exists on `<POU>`
- File naming: `I_[Lib]_[Purpose].TcIO` — e.g. `I_EB_BA_Widget.TcIO`
